{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: three source clients -> aggregation/orchestration -> summary-generator input. A unit test of one function is too narrow because the defect appears when wired components combine payloads. Higher levels are not required: behavior text is about payload assembly before generation, not real network/OS behavior, and not model output quality.","test_description":"Wire real collector/orchestration modules with deterministic in-process test doubles for the three sources, run one report build, and assert the exact payload sent to the summary-generation interface contains all three sections with source-specific key fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module error propagation and fallback rendering (source adapter failure -> report composer behavior). Unit is too low because the bug is in interaction. Rejected System: behavior text does not require validating real outage mechanics (timeouts/DNS/socket), only correct fallback behavior when a source is unavailable. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: correctness does not depend on model judgment or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Run the report pipeline in-process with one source adapter configured to fail (exception/503-like result) and other two succeeding; assert run completes, output includes `data unavailable` for only the failed section, and no global abort occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.17,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is model decision quality: whether generated narrative faithfully reflects input values. Mocked/stubbed generation would hide real failures (hallucination, omission, numeric drift), so Integration is insufficient. Rejected Workflow: behavior describes one generation judgment step, not multiple agentic stages in sequence.","test_description":"Use fixed representative report inputs and invoke the real summary model; score output against a factuality rubric (required key metrics/issues/deploy facts must be present and numerically correct) across repeated runs with acceptance thresholds for pass rate.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.79,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is end-to-end delivery across real infrastructure boundaries (networked APIs/email transport/inbox receipt). In-process fakes can miss real transport/auth/configuration failures. Rejected Agentic: behavior text targets successful inbox delivery of the pipeline, not evaluation of model output quality; a deterministic summary stub can still validate this boundary. Rejected Workflow: no requirement for multiple agentic decisions.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled report job in a staging environment with real source endpoints (or realistic staging counterparts) and real email delivery path to a test inbox; assert message arrival to configured recipient, subject/body structure correctness, and presence of all expected sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.84,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real infra behavior: unreachable email service plus persistence/retry across runs. Mocking can hide real connectivity/error-class handling and run-to-run durability issues. Rejected Integration: behavior explicitly involves service reachability and next scheduled run semantics, which are commonly where real OS/network/runtime conditions cause failures. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: this is delivery resilience, not model-quality-dependent decisions.","test_description":"Run job with email endpoint intentionally unreachable (e.g., blocked/stopped SMTP/API target) using real filesystem state; verify report file is persisted locally, then run the next scheduled invocation after restoring connectivity and assert pending report is retried and delivered exactly once.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.76,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
